						<div class="postbody">Indeed, modifying the APU to generate positive and negative is a way to do high-pass at the source. It eliminates the DC offset, but affects sound in other ways. The Game Boy Advance for example does this for the original GB sound channels, whereas the CGB and DMG aren't signed.</div>

